1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper proposes a novel event based stereo method that addresses the problem of motion blur for a moving event camera. Computer vision is a subfield of CS that deals with analyzing and interpreting images and videos. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper mentions the velocity of the camera, which suggests that the proposed method could be applied to robotics applications. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a novel matching cost over the time synchronized event disparity volumes, which could involve machine learning techniques. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a method that uses a range of disparities to synchronize the positions of the events, which could involve AI techniques. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a novel method that involves processing event disparity volumes, which could involve neural and evolutionary computing techniques.
